Package: mvmetrics
Type: Package
Title: Joint Performance Metrics for Mixed-Type Multivariate Responses
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2026-04-14
Authors@R: person("David", "Arango Londoño",
    email = "darango@unal.edu.co",
    role  = c("aut", "cre"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0000-0000-0000"))
Description: Provides a unified framework for evaluating joint predictive
    performance of models with mixed-type multivariate responses (continuous
    and binary). Implements five metric families: (A) Weighted Marginal Sum,
    (B) Multivariate Energy Score, (C) Variogram Score, (D) Marginal-Dependence
    Decomposition (MDD), and (E) Enhanced CV-Weighted Marginal-Dependence
    (E-CVWMD). The novel E-CVWMD metric assigns variable weights proportional
    to the coefficient of variation, computes a residual-correlation dependence
    score, and calibrates the marginal/dependence trade-off via a multivariate
    independence test. A single wrapper function accepts observed and predicted
    matrices for multiple models and returns a comprehensive report with rankings
    and metric recommendations. Bootstrap uncertainty quantification is included.
